^orange;怪物抗性^reset;
------------------------
有些怪物对特定类型的伤害有抗性，甚至完全免疫。

为了对抗这些威胁，你需要准备好^green;不同元素类型^reset;的武器。游戏中包含超过8种元素类型的武器，尝试使用^green;至少2到3种^reset;，这样你才能应对任何挑战。


^blue;--------------------------------------------------^reset;


^orange;武器与战斗^reset;
----------------------
在FrackinUniverse中，远程和近战武器的行为与原版有些不同，本指南中列举了最重要的变化。


^orange;暴击率和暴击伤害^reset;
---------------------------
武器物品提示中有新图标。左侧的两个图标代表暴击率加成和暴击伤害加成。


^orange;弹药和重新装填速度^reset;
---------------------------
弹药和重新装填速度由右侧图标表示。

如果以上属性中的任何一项显示为'--'，则表示该属性不适用于这些武器。这项变化主要适用于改装武器或能量武器。


^orange;精通^reset;
---------------

有时，你会在装备或种族加成中看到精通特性。这意味着你在某种武器类型上有更高的能力。通常来说，^yellow;精通^reset;只是^cyan;增强已有加成^reset;，包括科技加成。在下面即将介绍的主题中，你会看到各种武器及其带来的各种能力。这些列出的加成都会通过^yellow;精通^reset;得到提升。

例如：单独使用刺剑时，如果能仔细把握攻击时机，就会获得暴击率加成（最高为5）。应用的加成数量会根据你的^yellow;精通^reset;属性增加。达到100%时，就意味着暴击率加成最高为+10。
获得的加成因武器而异。在某些情况下，你会获得一个直接基于精通属性的加成，而在其他情况下，该数值会减半、四分之一、八分之一或其他类似的比例。



^blue;--------------------------------------------------^reset;


^green;远程^reset;
----------------------------------

^orange;使用弹药的武器^reset;
------------------
一些武器现在使用弹药。别担心，你不需要随身携带资源来重新装填这些武器。这些武器只是消耗更少的能量以换取额外的能量用于提升移动性！请注意，它们的替代射击总是需要能量，无论其主要射击如何。

你可以通过按住SHIFT键并点击鼠标进行手动重新装填。通过射击清空弹匣也会自动进行重新装填。

^orange;弹药精通^reset;
------------------
这项精通非常直接：你的弹药精通值直接与重新装填时间减少的百分比以及每个弹匣获得的弹药量相关。

^orange;手枪^reset;
------------------
拥有这项精通时，手枪伤害增加，重新装填时间减少，暴击率提升。

^orange;自动手枪^reset;
------------------
拥有这项精通时，自动手枪伤害增加，重新装填时间减少，暴击率提升。

^orange;臂炮^reset;
------------------
拥有这项精通时，臂炮根据其使用方式提供不同的加成。伤害、暴击率、暴击伤害和防御都会受到影响。单独使用臂炮时（单手或双手），你获得较少的防御加成，但暴击率更高。同时使用手臂和盾牌时，你获得更好的防御加成，但伤害减少。

^orange;突击步枪^reset;
------------------
拥有这项精通时，突击步枪整体伤害输出增加，同时弹匣容量和暴击伤害增加。

^orange;狙击步枪^reset;
------------------
精通狙击步枪时，你获得弹匣容量和暴击率加成。这与狙击步枪自带的暴击加成叠加，使得你在充能时获得非常高的暴击率！

^orange;榴弹发射器^reset;
------------------
拥有这项精通时，使用榴弹发射器时可以获得增加的伤害和弹匣容量，同时减少重新装填时间。

^orange;火箭筒^reset;
------------------
精通火箭筒时，你会对敌人造成更多伤害，重新装填速度更快，弹匣容量增加。

^orange;霰弹枪^reset;
------------------
这些危险的武器在精通时提供极高的暴击率和伤害，同时增加弹匣容量并减少重新装填时间。

^orange;磁力珠^reset;
------------------
这些不寻常的武器为精通者提供增加的伤害、暴击率、暴击伤害和能量。

^orange;弓^reset;
------------------
弓为精通者提供大量加成。增加伤害、暴击伤害和暴击率。此外，它们可以更快地发射，并消耗更少的能量！

^orange;鞭^reset;
------------------
鞭子精通者获得显著增加的暴击率和暴击伤害，同时增加伤害输出。


^green;近战^reset;
----------------------------------

^orange;连击^reset;
------------------
每次连击，无论是否击中目标，都会消耗1%的能量。请注意，眩晕敌人的战术不再那么可行。

许多连击武器在连击击中时提供额外的加成。

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;盾牌反伤^reset;
---------------
用盾牌格挡敌人时有机会进行盾牌反伤。某些装备可以增加盾牌反伤几率。

盾牌反伤可以对敌人造成伤害，并将其击退。当完美格挡时，有50%的几率眩晕成功盾牌反伤的敌人。如果不是完美格挡，请小心：一次糟糕的格挡有可能会让你自己被眩晕。

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;锤^reset;
---------------
这种武器的蓄力时间越长，暴击率和眩晕几率越高（最高可达^green;100^reset;%）。

蓄力超过^green;75^reset;%的锤会触发一次重击，能够眩晕并击飞敌人。

超过^green;100^reset;%的蓄力会自动取消加成。

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;巨斧^reset;
---------------
这种武器的蓄力时间越长，暴击率和暴击伤害越高（最高可达^green;100^reset;%）。

蓄力超过^green;75^reset;%的巨斧会触发一次重击，能够造成流血并击飞敌人。

超过^green;100^reset;%的蓄力会自动取消加成。

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;斧^reset;
---------------
每次连续击杀都会使你的最大伤害增加+^green;1^reset;%（最多^green;50^reset;%）。

如果你的生命值降到^red;20^reset;%以下，这个加成会取消。

每次连续命中都会使暴击率增加+^green;3^reset;%（最多^green;15^reset;%）。

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;匕首^reset;
---------------
连续快速击杀会暂时增加伤害

+^green;25^reset;% 闪避科技

连击增加防御和暴击率。防御加成在首次击中时最大，此后每次击中减少。

^cyan;双持（近战）:^reset; +^green;5^reset;% 移动速度

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;短剑^reset;
---------------
+1连击次数（原为2次，现在为3次）

每次连击增加你的暴击伤害

+^green;1^reset;% 连击暴击率

第一下连击暴击伤害增加+^green;15^reset;%。第二下连击暴击伤害增加+^green;25^reset;%。

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;巨剑^reset;
---------------
连续快速击杀会在短时间内增加防御

+^green;1^reset;% 连击暴击率

第一下连击暴击伤害增加+^green;15^reset;%。第二下连击暴击伤害增加+^green;25^reset;%。n
^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;镰刀^reset;
---------------
+^green;1^reset;% 连击暴击率

第一下连击暴击伤害增加+^green;5^reset;%。第二下连击暴击伤害增加+^green;25^reset;%。

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;长剑^reset;
---------------
第三下连击暴击伤害增加+^green;15^reset;%

^cyan;单手长剑^reset;: -^green;30^reset;% 连击冷却时间

^cyan;长剑 + 盾牌（双持）^reset;: +^green;4^reset;% 盾牌反伤，+^green;1^reset; 盾牌反伤击退距离，+^green;15^reset;% 治疗科技效率，+^green;25^reset;% 防御科技效率

^cyan;长剑 + 任何武器（双持）^reset;: 防御 x^red;0.8^reset;，+^green;5^reset;% 移动速度

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;刺剑^reset;
---------------
使用细剑时，攻击间隔越长，暴击率越高（最高为5）。攻击会重置这个加成。

^cyan;单手刺剑:^reset; +^green;15^reset;% 暴击伤害，+^green;35^reset;% 闪避和冲刺科技效率

^cyan;刺剑 + 匕首（双持）:^reset; x^green;1.12^reset; 防御，+^green;15^reset;% 闪避和冲刺科技效率

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;短矛^reset;
---------------
^cyan;单手短矛^reset;: +^green;30^reset;% 暴击伤害

^cyan;短矛 + 盾牌^reset;: +^green;10^reset;% 盾牌反伤，+^green;2^reset; 盾牌反伤击退距离，盾牌耐久恢复速度 x^green;1.2^reset;，+^green;50^reset;% 防御科技效率

^cyan;短矛 + 短矛（双持）^reset;: 防御 x^red;0.8^reset;，额外暴击率 x^red;0.5^reset;

短矛属于狩猎武器。

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;长矛^reset;
---------------
长矛相对简单。它们获得暴击率、更高的伤害输出和增加的冲刺科技效率。

按住攻击键可以保持矛的持有状态，以帮助抵挡敌人。如果使用长枪类型的矛，保持持有状态时，移动速度增加会增加伤害，此时无法瞄准。

长矛属于狩猎武器。

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;长棍^reset;
---------------
每次连击命中增加你的防御。

长矛属于狩猎武器。

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;钉头锤^reset;
---------------
连击增加2%的眩晕几率。

^cyan;单手钉头锤^reset;: +^green;2^reset;% 眩晕几率

^cyan;钉头锤 + 盾牌^reset;: +^green;3^reset;% 盾牌反伤，+^green;1^reset; 盾牌反伤击退距离，防御 x^green;1.1^reset;

^cyan;钉头锤 + 任何武器（双持）^reset;: 额外暴击率 x^red;0.85^reset;，额外眩晕几率 x^red;0.5^reset;，+^green;5^reset;% 移动速度

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;武士刀^reset;
---------------
每次挥击都会增加^green;1 + (连击步骤/10)^reset;% 的移动速度

连击增加抗击退能力

^cyan;单手武士刀^reset;: +^green;15^reset;% 防御科技效率

^cyan;武士刀 + 重型近战武器（双持）^reset;: 伤害 x^red;0.8^reset;，防御 x^red;0.9^reset;

^cyan;武士刀 + 轻型近战武器（双持）^reset;: 能量 x^green;1.15^reset;，+^green;20^reset;% 暴击伤害，+^green;25^reset;% 闪避和冲刺科技效率

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;拳套^reset;
---------------
普通攻击每次消耗^red;3%能量^reset;。按住按钮会激活这种模式。

连击需要时机：按住或快速点击按键会使用普通攻击。

连击增加暴击率^green;1%^reset;、眩晕几率^green;4%^reset;和每次击中增加防御。当攻击时，它们消耗^red;1%^reset;能量。

替代攻击/终结技通过^cyan;[Shift + 点击]^reset;触发。在连击之外使用时消耗^red;15%^reset;能量。完成连击作为最后一击时不消耗能量。


^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;附录^reset;
---------------
额外暴击/眩晕几率指的是武器本身不具备的统计数据，例如来自护甲或消耗品的加成。

Texts.Eng:
^orange;Monster Resistances^reset;
------------------------
Some monsters resist, or are completely immune to, certain types of damage.

To combat these threats you are going to need weapons of ^green;different elemental types^reset; at any given moment. Try to use ^green;at least 2 to 3^reset; of the more than 8 available types so you are ready for any challenge.


^blue;--------------------------------------------------^reset;


^orange;Weapons and Combat^reset;
----------------------
Ranged and Melee weapons behave a little differently in FrackinUniverse. The most important changes are listed in this codex.


^orange;Crit Chance and Crit Damage^reset;
---------------------------
Weapon item tooltips have new icons. The two on the left represent Critical Chance bonus and Critical Damage bonus.


^orange;Ammo and Reload Speed^reset;
---------------------------
Ammo and Reload speed are represented by the right-side icons.

Items with a '--' representing a value in any of the above stats means it does not apply to them. This is the case with modded weapons, or energy-only (non-ammo) guns, primarily.


^orange;Mastery^reset;
---------------

Occasionally, you'll see Mastery traits applied to equippable gear, or in Racial Bonuses. These imply that you have greater capability in a particular weapon type. Generally speaking, ^yellow;Masteries^reset; simply ^cyan;improve already existing weapon benefits^reset; including Tech bonuses. In an upcoming topic below, you'll see various weapons listed along with the various capabilities each carries with it. These listed benefits will all be improved through ^yellow;Mastery^reset;.

An example: When wielded individually a Rapier will provide an increase to Crit Chance when timing strikes carefully (to a max of 5). The amount of the bonus applied is higher by the amount listed in your ^yellow;Mastery^reset; stat. At 100% this would mean a maximum Crit Chance bonus of +10.

The amount of benefit gained can vary from weapon to weapon. In some cases you will get a modifier based directly on your ^yellow;Mastery^reset; trait, while others will reduce that value by half, quarter, eigth or other such fractions.



^blue;--------------------------------------------------^reset;


^green;Ranged^reset;
----------------------------------

^orange;Ammo-Based Weapons^reset;
------------------
Some weapons now use ammunition. Don't worry, you won't need to carry resources around with you to refill them. These weapons simply use much, much less energy in exchange for the mobility boost provided by having extra energy! Note that their alt fires will always require energy, regardless of their primary fire.

You can reload these weapons manually by holding the SHIFT key and clicking the mouse button. Emptying the magazine through shooting will also automatically engage the reload.

^orange;Ammo Mastery^reset;
------------------
This Mastery is quite straightforward: your rating in Ammo Mastery directly correlates to the % reduced from your Reload Time as well as the $ of ammo gained per magazine.

^orange;Pistol^reset;
------------------
With mastery applied, Pistols gain increased Damage, reduced reload time and a higher critical strike chance.

^orange;Machine Pistol^reset;
------------------
With mastery applied, Machine Pistols gain increased Damage, reduced reload time and a higher critical strike chance.

^orange;Arm Cannon^reset;
------------------
With mastery applied, Arm Cannons provide varied benefits based on how they are wielded. Power, Crit Chance, Crit Damage and Protection are all impacted. When using just arm cannons (dual or single) you get less protection benefits but a much higher critical chance. With an armcannon and shield you gain a much better protection bonus in exchange for reduced power.

^orange;Assault Rifle^reset;
------------------
Assault rifles benefit from mastery by increasing overall damage output while increasing magazine size and critical damage.

^orange;Sniper Rifle^reset;
------------------
With a mastery in Sniper rifles you gain magazine size and critical chance. This stacks with the usual crit benefits of sniper rifles and allows for a very high crit chance with charge-ups!

^orange;Grenade Launcher^reset;
----------------------
When wielding grenade launchers with mastery expect to gain increased damage and magazine size while also benefiting from reduced reload time.

^orange;Rocket Launcher^reset;
----------------------
Obliterating the enemy is easy with mastery in rockets! You'll do a lot more damage, reload faster and have increased magazine size.

^orange;Shotgun^reset;
----------------------
These dangerous weapons, when mastered, profice exceptional crit chance and power along with increased magazine size and reduced reload time.

^orange;Magnorb^reset;
----------------------
These unusual weapons provide increased damage, crit chance, crit damage and energy to masters that wield them.

^orange;Bow^reset;
----------------------
Bows have a large number of benefits masters can take advantage of. Crit damage and crit chance increase, along with damage. In addition, they can fire bows faster and shoot arrows farther while consuming less energy!

^orange;Whip^reset;
----------------------
Whip users get a sizeable increase in crit chance and crit damage while also increasing damage output with this mastered weapon.


^blue;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^green;Melee^reset;

^orange;Combos^reset;
---------------
Each strike of a combo, whether or not it hits a target, consumes 1% of your energy. Be warned, tactics involving stun-locking enemies are no longer as viable.

Many weapons with combos provide additional bonuses when striking with these combos.

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Shield Bash^reset;
---------------
Blocking with shields on enemies has a chance to Shield Bash. Certain gear can increase the Shield Bash chances.

Shield Bash can damage foes, and send them reeling backwards. When Perfect Blocking, there is a 50% chance to Stun foes that are successfully bashed. When not perfect blocking, be wary: There is a chance -you- will get stunned on a badly timed block.

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Hammer^reset;
---------------
The longer you hold the charge of this melee weapon type, the higher your Critical and Stun chance get (to a maximum of ^green;100^reset;%).

A hammer charged above ^green;75^reset;% will inflict a massive bonus eruption capable of stunning and tossing foes around.

Over-Charging the hammer past ^green;100^reset;% will automatically cancel the bonus.

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Great Axe^reset;
---------------
The longer you hold the charge of this melee weapon type, the higher your Critical Chance and Critical Damage get (to a maximum of ^green;100^reset;%).

A greataxe charged above ^green;75^reset;% will inflict a massive bonus eruption capable of bleeding and tossing foes around.

Over-Charging the greataxe past ^green;100^reset;% will automatically cancel the bonus.

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Axe^reset;
---------------
Each consecutive kill made with an axe increases your maximum damage by +^green;1^reset;%, to a maximum of ^green;50^reset;%.

If your health is reduced below ^red;20^reset;%, this bonus is cancelled.

Each consecutive hit in a row with an axe increases Crit Chance by +^green;3^reset;% (to a maximum of ^green;15^reset;%)

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Dagger^reset;
---------------
Consecutive rapid kills temporarily increase damage

+^green;25^reset;% Dodge Tech Efficiency

Combo Strikes increase Protection and Crit Chance with each strike. The protection bonus is greatest on First Strike, and reduces each hit thereafter.

^cyan;Dual-Wield (Melee):^reset; +^green;5^reset;% Movement Speed


^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Shortsword^reset;
---------------
+1 Combo strike (was 2, now 3)

Each combo hit increases your Crit Damage amount

+^green;1^reset;% Crit Chance per Combo Strike

First Combo strike does +^green;15^reset;% Crit Damage. Second hit does +^green;25^reset;% Crit Damage.

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Broadsword^reset;
---------------
Kills made in rapid succession increase defense for a short time

+^green;1^reset;% Crit Chance per Combo Strike

First Combo strike does +^green;15^reset;% Crit Damage. Second hit does +^green;25^reset;% Crit Damage.

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Scythe^reset;
---------------
+^green;1^reset;% Crit Chance per Combo Strike

First Combo strike does +^green;15^reset;% Crit Damage. Second hit does +^green;25^reset;% Crit Damage.

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Longsword^reset;
---------------
3rd Combo Strike does +^green;15^reset;% Crit Damage

^cyan;Single Longsword^reset;: -^green;30^reset;% Combo Cooldown

^cyan;Longsword + Shield (Dual Wield)^reset;: +^green;4^reset;% Shield Bash, +^green;1^reset; Shield Bash Push Distance, +^green;15^reset;% Healing Tech Efficiency, +^green;25^reset;% Defense Tech Efficiency

^cyan;Longsword + Any Weapon (Dual Wield)^reset;: Defense x^red;0.8^reset;, +^green;5^reset;% Movement Speed

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Rapier^reset;
---------------
When wielding a rapier, the longer you wait between swings the higher your critical strike chance becomes (to a maximum of 5). Attacking resets this bonus.

^cyan;Single Rapier:^reset; +^green;15^reset;% Crit Damage, +^green;35^reset;% Dodge and Dash Tech Efficiency

^cyan;Rapier + Dagger (Dual Wield):^reset; x^green;1.12^reset; Protection, +^green;15^reset;% Dodge and Dash Tech Efficiency

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Shortspear^reset;
---------------
^cyan;Single Shortspear^reset;: +^green;30^reset;% Crit Damage

^cyan;Shortspear + Shield^reset;: +^green;10^reset;% Shield Bash, +^green;2^reset; Shield Push Distance, Shield Regen x^green;1.2^reset;, +^green;50^reset;% Defense Tech Efficiency

^cyan;Shortspear + Shortspear (Dual Wield)^reset;: Defense x^red;0.8^reset;, Bonus Crit Chance x^red;0.5^reset;

Short Spears also count as Hunting weapons.

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Spear^reset;
---------------
Spears are relatively straightforward. They gain crit chance, higher damage output and an increase in Dash Tech efficiency.

Spears can be held out by holding the fire button to help keep enemies at bay. If using a Lance typed spear you also gain increased damage based on your movement speed while holding it out. It cannot be aimed during this.

Spears also count as Hunting weapons.

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Quarterstaff^reset;
---------------
Each hit with a combo increases your Defense.

^#555555;--------------------------------------------------^reset;
^orange;Mace^reset;
---------------
Combo strikes increase Stun Chance by 2% per hit.

^cyan;Single Mace^reset;: +^green;2^reset;% Stun Chance

